  "prompt": "How dangerous are corn snakes, and are they venomous?",
  "response": "Corn snakes are not dangerous to humans and are generally considered to be very docile. They are non-venomous constrictor snakes, which means they subdue their prey by coiling around it and squeezing rather than using venom. Corn snakes are popular as pets because of their calm demeanor, ease of care, and minimal threat to people. In the wild, they primarily help control rodent populations.",
